Looking through the API documentation, I have found that for pull requests there is what appears to be an excellent and complete resource for activity.

{code}
https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/repositories/{owner}/{repo_slug}/pullrequests/activity
{code}

However, I have not found similar resources for changesets or issues.

The only resource I have found that provides similar functionality is the API 1.0 "events" resource, which in theory provides the information I want to request but is _severely_ lacking (not even providing IDs for many types of events, whereas the pull-requests activity resource includes useful links).

